#### Roadmap:

Within the network, there are 4 phases in its lifecycle. The initial phase is the most bare-bones version of the network. It will be simply reporting a scam and users being able to see it. There will be no other user interaction beyond that in order to have some variation of a product. This will be for the initial 6 months of the project. 
The second phase implements verification and roles. Users will be able to verify reports as well as earn the verifier, reporter, and even potentially the moderator role. This is also where reporting and moderation comes into play. This will span over the next 6 months of the project as well to develop the verification and status algorithms. 
The third phase is where community engagement is large enough to develop forums to provide resources and engagement for the community. Users can share stories, guides, social media posts, spread awareness, etc. This is also where update logs, announcements, and transparent communication are. This will span over the next 3 years of the project, with minor feature enhancements and changes regarding user design and various feedback we would receive. 
The last phase is major expansion within the life of the project. There are many possibilities for this. A major one would be automation such as AI. Using automation can be used to verify scams by using AI to call or contact the source from the reports. This way scams can be updated even more in real time than before. AI can also be utilized to analyze patterns to potentially pinpoint the source of the scam more accurately. In addition, the network can be integrated into various platforms to automatically block scams. For example, if the scam is on Facebook messenger and an individual reports that account and the report is verified, the platform can automatically ban the account to prevent others from being scammed.

